description.narrative:
Indicator 1.
1. Availability of the baseline assessment/ analysis of the economic impact of climate change to agriculture sector, export potential and regional development including gender considerations;
2. # of recommendations on consideration of climate induced risks in regional development planning with focus on agro-business and export potential and gender considerations;
3. Availability of Regional Development Strategies and Action plan to integrate adaptive measures against climate change risks in agricultural sector;
4. # of counterparts (30/70 ratio from overall number) trained on issues of integrating climate change and sustainable use of natural resources into local and sector development programmes;
5. Availability of the Concept on integrated pest management/control through the introduction of local agro-meteo stations;
6. # of recommendations on location specific adaptive agricultural systems to climate risks for agro-development planning and forecasting;
7. Availability of software for land planning, forecasting of crop yield and export volumes for agro-planners

Indicator 2:
1. Availability of the assessment/study on benefits of using modern meteo-stations in horticulture and other agricultural activities to mitigate the climate risks to livelihoods of rural agriculture producers;
2. Established network of extension services to provide assistance to agro-producing clients to be more risk informed and prepared for climate change impacts;
3. Availability of a study with recommendations on development of the agro-insurance sector;  
4. # of pilot projects supported with cost sharing contribution to support small scale agro-production;
5. # of women/youth engaged in pilot projects (30/70 ratio from overall number) using efficient agricultural practices/innovative solutions with consideration of climate change risks;
6. # of agro-meteo-stations established to provide  local meteo-data for farmers and households;
7. # of agro-producers trained on marketin

comment.narrative:
Baseline 1.
1. No baseline assessment/ analysis of the economic impact of climate change to agriculture sector is available;
2. No recommendations exist on consideration of climate induced risks in regional development planning;
3. Existing Regional Development Strategies with no climate change considerations; 
4. No representatives of local counterparts are trained on issues of integrating climate change and sustainable use of natural resources into local and sector development programmes;
5. No Concept on integrated pest management/control is available;
6. No recommendations on location specific adaptive agricultural systems to climate risks for agro-development planning and forecasting;
7. No software exist for land planning, forecasting of crop yield and export volumes for agro-planners

Baseline 2:
1. No assessment/study available on benefits of using modern meteo-stations in horticulture and other agricultural activities;
2. No network of extension services exist to provide assistance to agro-producing clients;
3. No study with recommendations on development of the agro-insurance sector;
4. No pilot projects supported in small scale agro-production;
5. No women/youth using efficient agricultural practices/innovative solutions with consideration of climate change risks;
6. No agro-meteo-stations established  to provide local meteo-data for farmers and households in target areas;
7. No agro-producers trained on marketing, export opportunities, insurance

Output 1.
1. Baseline established and Impact Assessment submitted to project counterparts;
2. At least 2 recommendations on consideration of climate induced risks in regional development planning; 
3. Draft revised Regional Strategy/Action Plan proposed for Government;
4. At least 30 counterparts (30/70 ratio from overall number) trained on issues of integrating climate change and sustainable use of natural resources into local and sector development programmes;
5. Draft Concept on integrated pest management has been developed and submitted to the counterparts for consideration;
6. At least 5 recommendations on location specific adaptive agricultural systems to climate risks;
7. First pilot version of software developed and tested;

Output 2:
1. The extension network established and service provider(s) equipped with required basic equipment;
2. The study on agro-insurance sector held, and report submitted to CCI;
3. At least 6 pilot projects supported with cost sharing contribution to support small scale agro-production;
4. At least 10 women/youth engaged in pilot projects (30/70 ratio from overall number) using efficient agricultural practices/innovative solutions with consideration of climate change risks;
5. At least 9 agrometeorological stations installed to provide local meteo-data for farmers and households;
6. At least 60 agro-producers trained on advanced agricultural practices, marketing and agro-meteorological stations (with women’s participation – 30/70 ratio)

Output 1.
1. Methodology/concept for study developed;
2. At least 1 recommendation on consideration of climate induced risks in regional development planning; 
3. Working group formally formed and initial review of the existing Regional Development Strategy has been done;
4. Draft Concept on integrated pest management has been developed and submitted to the counterparts for consideration;
5. At least 3 recommendations on location specific adaptive agricultural systems to climate risks;
6. ToR for application on land planning, forecasting of crop yield and export volumes for agro-planners developed and submitted to CCI;

Output 2:
1. The Assessment/Study on benefits of using modern meteo-stations in horticulture submitted to project counterparts;
2. The MOU signed with selected extension services provider/s;
3. Methodology on agro-insurance sector development is proposed and agreed with CCI;
4. Business ideas selection procedure and criteria are proposed and agreed with CCI;
5. At least 60 agro-producers trained on advanced agricultural practices and agro-meteorological stations (with women’s participation – 30/70 ratio)
